00:43:32,072 --> 00:43:35,094
That doesn't mean there isn't something, you know, going to get dropped on my lap tomorrow.

430
00:43:35,909 --> 00:43:38,691
Because that seems to be the way it happens a lot of times.

431
00:43:39,652 --> 00:43:44,376
I like it when people actually give me advance warning, but sometimes they don't.

432
00:43:45,277 --> 00:43:46,358
So, all right.

433
00:43:46,398 --> 00:43:47,159
So I think we're good then.

434
00:43:47,339 --> 00:43:53,304
I'll send you... I meant to send you guys the last few days about the stuff for next week.

435
00:43:53,324 --> 00:43:56,527
So I'll send that to you before I leave tonight for next week.

436
00:43:56,807 --> 00:44:02,952
And I will see some of you then, others... I have a motion to close the hearing.

437
00:44:03,072 --> 00:44:03,213
Yes.

438
00:44:05,224 --> 00:44:06,625
I'll make a motion to close the hearing.

439
00:44:07,946 --> 00:44:09,647
Second.

440
00:44:09,968 --> 00:44:11,148
All in favor, Caroline.

441
00:44:11,669 --> 00:44:11,829
Aye.

442
00:44:12,389 --> 00:44:12,890
Craig.

443
00:44:13,490 --> 00:44:13,630
Aye.

444
00:44:14,431 --> 00:44:14,731
Eric.

445
00:44:15,472 --> 00:44:15,612
Aye.

446
00:44:16,092 --> 00:44:16,753
Myself, aye.

447
00:44:17,453 --> 00:44:17,833
All right.

448
00:44:19,535 --> 00:44:20,075
Now we can go.

449
00:44:20,115 --> 00:44:21,836
Bye, everyone.

450
00:44:23,017 --> 00:44:23,217
Bye.

451
00:44:23,257 --> 00:44:24,098
